# 🏥 Insurance Cost Prediction using Machine Learning

A data preprocessing and exploratory data analysis (EDA) project focused on predicting **medical insurance charges** based on demographic and lifestyle factors.

This repository currently contains the complete data analysis and feature engineering pipeline. Machine Learning model training and evaluation will be added in the next phase.

---

## 📌 Project Objective

The goal of this project is to build a Machine Learning model capable of predicting an individual's **medical insurance charges** using features such as:

- Age
- Gender
- BMI (Body Mass Index)
- Number of Children
- Smoking Status
- Residential Region

Before training the model, the dataset is explored, cleaned, and transformed to ensure high-quality inputs for Machine Learning algorithms.

---

## 📂 Dataset

**Dataset Used:** `insurance.csv`

The dataset contains demographic and health-related information along with the corresponding insurance charges.

### Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| age | Age of the individual |
| sex | Gender |
| bmi | Body Mass Index |
| children | Number of dependent children |
| smoker | Smoking status |
| region | Residential region |
| charges | Medical insurance charges (Target Variable) |

---

## 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

The notebook includes:

- Dataset overview
- Data shape and information
- Missing value inspection
- Duplicate value checking
- Statistical summary
- Distribution analysis
- Correlation analysis
- Outlier detection
- Feature relationships with insurance charges

Various visualizations are used to better understand how each feature influences insurance costs.

---

## ⚙️ Feature Engineering

The preprocessing pipeline includes:

- Handling categorical variables
- Encoding categorical features
- Feature extraction
- Data transformation
- Preparing the dataset for Machine Learning

The final processed dataset is suitable for training regression models.

